Twice-weekly automation scan at 03:00 AM ET, Mondays and Thursdays. Grooming pass focused on workflow → code conversions.

Read `_Iris_Memory/Sessions/CLAUDE_CODE_HANDOFF.md` for context. Hard rules from `06_CEO/Designs/2026-05-26_Claude_Code_Engineering_Handoff.md` apply.

Read `06_CEO/Automation_Backlog.md` — this is the canonical ranked list. Maintain it in place.

Perform these four passes:

1. **Backlog re-evaluation.** For each ⚪ pending item: has state changed (deps shipped, priority rationale obsolete, effort estimate updated, item now blocked or unblocked)? Update inline. For each 🟡 in-progress item: still moving or stuck? Promote/demote priority tags accordingly.
   - **Verify status against LIVE state, don't trust the row.** A backlog row's status can lag reality — an item marked ⚪ pending may already be shipped. Before re-ranking, spot-check ⚪ items against the actual system: `grep` iris.py for the proposed change, check whether the target file/dir/script already exists, check `git log`/`git status` in `/Volumes/AI_Workspace/iris_studio/`. (Reading/grep only — the hard build-ban still holds.) Lesson from the 2026-05-28 first run: A-8 was marked ⚪ but had shipped on 2026-05-27; only a grep of iris.py caught it.
   - **Watch the 60-min nightly→scan window.** This routine fires at 03:00 ET; the autonomous engineering routine (`com.iris.claude-code-nightly`) fires at 02:00 ET daily. **Items shipped by the nightly between 02:00-03:00 will be on disk before THIS scan runs** — and need explicit reconciliation, NOT promotion as new. Also re-verify ANY new candidate you draft this run against on-disk state before adding the row: drafted at 03:01 may already be shipped by 03:02. Lesson from the 2026-06-01 second run: A-19 (.docx→.md) was drafted as a new 🔥 candidate, then the on-disk file-date check found Session 20 had shipped it at 02:58 ET — 2 min before the scan fired. Adding a fresh "verify candidate is not already shipped" check before each new-candidate row averts the repeat.

2. **New candidate discovery.** Re-read:
   - INBOX.md (any items added since last scan — note the 6/10 format contract caps it at ≤150 lines)
   - **`06_CEO/Decision_Queue.md` — all open rows.** Added 2026-06-11 5th run after the 6/10 brain refactor codified Principle 4 (Default Action Autonomy). Steve-call decisions now live here, not in INBOX subsections. The routine should scan open DQ rows to (a) see whether any pending decision has an automation-shaped angle that should become an A-row, (b) avoid duplicating items already DQ-tracked, (c) cross-reference the routine's promotions against the canonical Steve-action surface. DO NOT write to Decision_Queue from THIS routine unless surfacing a brand-new Steve-call candidate (Pass 3) — closing/updating open rows is the vault gardener's lane.
   - STEVE_CONTEXT.md date-bumps in the last 7 days
   - The last 7 `_Iris_Memory/Daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md` notes
   - The 3 most recent `_Iris_Memory/Sessions/*_Nightly_Value_Pulse.md` digests (if present)
   - The 3 most recent `_Iris_Memory/Sessions/CLAUDE_CODE_HANDOFF.md` bridge entries
   - **`_Iris_Memory/Projects/Pitch_Log.md` — last 7 days of entries.** Cowork-Iris's nightly pulses log pitches there; pitches explicitly framed for Claude Code's lane (text patterns: "Engineering — Claude Code's lane", "iris.py hook", "multi-file build", "will surface in the digest so the automation-scan picks it up") are direct backlog candidates. Lesson from the 2026-06-04 third run: Pitch #20 (agent output-linter, logged 2026-06-03) was framed by Cowork as "Engineering — Claude Code's lane (multi-file / iris.py hook); logging here + will surface in the digest so the automation-scan picks it up" — this routine then absorbed it as A-23. **2026-06-10 governance shift: Pitch_Log is now zero-⚪ by policy** (brain-refactor triage); new pitches needing Steve calls land as Decision_Queue rows. This file remains the audit-trail + closure-tracker source — useful for verifying that prior pitches landed as A-rows or DQ rows, not the new-candidate firehose it used to be.

   Look for:
   - Manual processes Steve mentioned doing (text patterns: "I do X every", "I forgot to", "I have to remember")
   - Pain points (text patterns: "this is annoying", "wish I didn't have to", "manually")
   - Iris-stack drift: duplicate scripts, routines firing but invisible to Steve, files growing unbounded, manual steps Steve takes between Iris-runs
   - New tech additions that could be auto-monitored or auto-maintained
   - Cowork pitches in Claude Code's lane (per the Pitch_Log read above)

   Add each as a new candidate row in `Automation_Backlog.md` with: manual-today, proposed automation, saves, effort, dependencies, priority tag.

3. **Promote top picks — Decision_Queue rows, NOT INBOX subsections (updated 2026-06-11).** Pick the 1-2 highest-leverage 🔥 items where deps are met and effort is under 2 hours.
   - **For Steve-call items:** add a row to `06_CEO/Decision_Queue.md` (with `Class` per Principle 4: AUTO / 💰 SPEND / 📤 EXTERNAL / 🎨 CREATIVE / ⚖️ LEGAL), state Iris's default action, set a 72h deadline, and link the backlog row. The C2 stale-on-you surface (Session 33, pre-brief Pass 15) picks up the row at next 05:00 ET fire and the morning brief absorbs it. **Why the change:** the 6/10 brain refactor + INBOX format contract (≤150 lines, actions+pointers only, no digest narration) made the prior `## 🤖 Iris-recommended automations` subsection mechanic incompatible — and Principle 4 gave Steve a structural place to land decisions instead of having items go stale for 14+ days. Lesson from tonight's 5th run: the 6/8 codified Steve-revealed-preference de-promote rule never fired against A-17 because the 6/9 spec approval shipped the meta-fix one day before. **Surface contracts beat day-counters.** When the operating system around the routine evolves, the routine's surfaces must match within 1-2 scans or its outputs become friction instead of leverage.
   - **For auto-build-eligible items:** no Steve surface change needed — tag the backlog row `auto-build-eligible: true` and the nightly engineering routine picks it up after Day 4.
   - **Legacy INBOX subsection:** do NOT create a new `## 🤖 Iris-recommended automations` subsection on top of the C2 block. If a prior run left one, leave it for the vault gardener to clean up — don't touch INBOX from this routine going forward unless absolutely necessary.
   - Don't repeat items already promoted in the past 2 weeks unless Steve still hasn't acted — then re-surface with a higher urgency note (now as an updated DQ row, NOT a new INBOX line) AND apply the auto-build-eligible escalation below.
   - **Escalation rule for stale promotions (Day-2, tightened 2026-06-13 from Day-4 per Redesign A5; original Day-4 rule added 2026-06-01):** If a promoted ⚪ item has aged past **2 days** without Steve's ✅ or 🔴, AND the item meets the **safe-for-autonomous** criteria (no creds touched, no public listeners added, no Steve-only OAuth required, pure-defense or pure-content), tag the backlog row with `auto-build-eligible: true` and explicitly note in the DQ row / re-surface that the item will ship on the next nightly engineering fire unless 🔴-declined. This preserves THIS routine's surface-only mandate while not letting good resilience work die in the queue. Items NOT qualifying for safe-for-autonomous (anything touching creds, public listeners, daemon dispatch loop, sponsor-facing outputs, money flows) stay un-tagged and require explicit Steve ✅.
   - **Why Day-2 not Day-4 (Redesign A5 rationale):** With V1 (semantic-status contract) + V2 (pre-brief fire-diff + routine digest) now live, the safety case for waiting 4 days on auto-build-eligible items weakened. V1 catches blocked/partial deliverables at dispatch time (within seconds of the failure); V2 catches silent-skip cadences inside ≤24h. The eligibility criteria themselves are unchanged — only the wait-window before auto-build fires. Day-2 still gives Steve a fair surface window (Mon promote → Wed nightly build at earliest) but ends the multi-week-stale pattern that Day-4 produced in 5/28→6/8.
   - **Steve-revealed-preference de-promotion rule (added 2026-06-08):** For NOT-auto-build-eligible 🔥 items that have been promoted in 4+ consecutive scans (≥ 14 days) without Steve ✅ or 🔴, demote the backlog row 🔥 → 🟧 with a "[de-promoted YYYY-MM-DD by Steve-revealed-preference rule]" note. STOP re-surfacing the item in the INBOX `🤖 Iris-recommended automations` subsection. Move it to a quiet "Long-standing 🔥 items awaiting explicit decision" line at the bottom of that subsection with the explicit ask: "Steve — please ✅, 🔴, or tell me to de-promote." This honors the implicit prioritization signal (no action in 14+ days = lower priority than the 🔥 tag claims) AND forces a binary decision instead of infinite re-surface. Lesson from the 2026-06-08 4th run: A-17 was promoted in 4 consecutive scans (5/28 + 6/1 + 6/4 + 6/8) with louder Day-N framing each time and zero Steve action; "louder text" is not an escalation path — the routine should bias toward Steve's revealed preferences over its own ranking after a fair surface window. Counter-rule: if Steve EXPLICITLY says "carry it" or ✅s in chat without shipping, the day-counter resets; this rule only fires for SILENT non-engagement.

4. **Meta-improvement on the routine itself.** Reflect: did last week's promoted candidates get Steve's action? If not, why? Was the framing wrong, the effort estimate off, the dependency unclear? Update this prompt file (the one you are reading) if a process change is warranted. This is the "improve the improvement loop" pass.

**Output expectations:**
- `06_CEO/Automation_Backlog.md` updated in place (priority shifts, new rows, deduplicated). Stale promotions re-surfaced with their `auto-build-eligible: true` tag where applicable.
- `06_CEO/Decision_Queue.md` may get 1-2 new rows for newly-promoted Steve-call items (updated 2026-06-11 — replaces the prior INBOX subsection mechanic). Each row: ID (DQ-N, next available), Decision, Class, Default, Deadline (72h), Days pending (0), Status (⏳ open).
- INBOX.md should generally NOT be touched by this routine going forward (the C2 stale-on-you surface picks up DQ rows automatically). Exception: if a new automation row is shipped IMMEDIATELY by this routine (impossible per the hard ban — surface-only), OR if a legacy `## 🤖 Iris-recommended automations` subsection exists from a prior run, leave it for the gardener.
- New session digest at `_Iris_Memory/Sessions/YYYY-MM-DD_automation-scan.md` with frontmatter (`type: session`, `agent: claude-code`, `routine: automation-scan`) + four-pass summary + which items were promoted to Decision_Queue (or shipped to ⚪→🟢 reconciliation in the case of a great-reconciliation run like 2026-06-11's).
- Append one line to today's daily note under `## 🤖 Claude Code intra-day log`. Format: `HH:MM — automation scan: N reconciled, M promoted → Sessions/...`.

**Hard ban on building.** This routine surfaces + ranks only. No code changes, no plist deploys, no daemon edits. Builds happen in the nightly engineering routine — either after Steve ✅s a candidate via Telegram or in-session, OR (per the 2026-06-01 escalation rule) when an `auto-build-eligible: true` tagged item ages past 4 days without 🔴.

**C2 cross-cadence rule (Redesign Night 4, 2026-06-12).** The C2 stale-on-you block in `INBOX.md` (between `<!-- C2_STALE_ON_YOU:BEGIN -->` markers, refreshed by pre-brief Pass 15) is the single canonical "awaiting Steve" surface. When this routine's session digest narrates pending Steve-call items: if the item is already a DQ row, reference DQ-N by id (one line) and let the C2 surface carry the day-counter — do NOT re-list with a fresh per-cadence day-count or unlock-value rationale. New Steve-call candidates this routine promotes land as DQ rows (per Pass 3) and join the C2 surface automatically at next 05:00 ET; the routine's own digest should not duplicate the same surface in narrative form. Pre-brief verifies the surface freshness; this routine writes new entries to it; hygiene references it. Three cadences, one canonical surface.
